<title>
DTC B1951
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
As each terminal voltage is affected by the battery voltage, check that battery voltage is 12 V or more with ignition ON.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Before performing, be sure to confirm that related fuses of headlight auto leveling and washer control module power circuit have not blown out. 
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If any fuse has blown out, replace the fuse and check circuits connected to the blown fuse for short circuit to ground.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
